Function Details [hide private]

generate_swirl(N, L, zmin, zmax, cycle_rate, bias_x, bias_y, roll_num=0, noise=0, fromcentre=True)

source code 

Generate N points on a 3D 'swirl' (a cyclic trajectory on a 1 x L "swiss roll" manifold).

cycle_rate is measured in radians. roll_num is the number of full rolls in the swiss roll.

The origin is at the centre of the set unless fromcentre=False.

generate_discspiral(N1, N2, D, radius, cycle_rate, num_spirals=1, noise=0)

source code 

Generate N1 points on a planar disc and N2 points on up to two spirals attached to it, also in the plane. The data are embedded in an ambient space of dimension D. The cycle_rate (radians per point) determines how much of the spiral is created. num_spirals can be 0, 1, or 2

generate_spiral(N, D, radius, cycle_rate, expand_rate=1.0, num_spirals=1, noise=0)

source code 

Generate N points on up to two spirals in the plane. The data are embedded in an ambient space of dimension D. The cycle_rate (radians per point) determines how much of the spiral is created. radius is the starting radius of the spiral. num_spirals can be 0, 1, or 2

generate_hypercube(N, D, length, fromcentre=True)

source code 

Generate a length-N uniformly-distributed random set of data points in a D-dimensional hypercube having side-length given by third parameter.

The origin is at the centre of the set unless fromcentre=False.

generate_ball(N, D, radius)

source code 

Generate a length-N uniformly-distributed random set of data points in a D-dimensional ball of radius given by the third parameter. Points are found by elimination of points from hypercubes and thus this method is not recommended for large D!
